<div class="navheader"><table width="100%" summary="Navigation header"><tr><th colspan="3" align="center">Keyboard Task - Enable and Disable a Keyboard</th></tr><tr><td width="20%" align="left"><a accesskey="p" href="basic_enable_keyboard.php">Prev</a> </td><th width="60%" align="center">Chapter 3. Basic Help</th><td width="20%" align="right"> <a accesskey="n" href="basic_uninstall_keyboard.php">Next</a></td></tr></table><hr></div><div class="section" lang="en"><div class="titlepage"><div><div><h2 class="title" style="clear: both" id="basic_disable_keyboard">Keyboard Task - Enable and Disable a Keyboard</h2></div></div></div><p>Keyman keyboards can be enabled and disabled.</p><h3><a name="id569090"></a>Disabling a Keyman keyboard</h3><p>Disabling a Keyman keyboard removes it from the Keyman menu and Keyman Toolbox but does not uninstall the keyboard. This is useful if:</p><div class="itemizedlist"><ul type="disc"><li><p>You are using a single keyboard layout from a package with multiple keyboards and you want to remove the extra keyboards from the Keyman Toolbox and menu.</p></li><li><p>You have a keyboard layout installed which you aren't currently using but don't want to uninstall.</p></li></ul></div><p>To disable a Keyman keyboard:</p><div class="orderedlist"><ol type="1"><li><p>Open <span class="application">Keyman Desktop</span>.</p></li><li><p>Click on the <span class="guiicon">Keyman Desktop</span> icon <span class="inlinemediaobject"><img src="desktop_images/icon-keyman.png"></span>, on the Windows Taskbar near the clock.</p><p>
        <span class="inlinemediaobject"><img src="desktop_images/menu.png"></span>
      </p></li><li><p>Select Configuration.</p><p>
        <span class="inlinemediaobject"><img src="desktop_images/tab-layout.png"></span>
      </p></li><li><p>Select the Keyboard Layouts tab.</p></li><li><p>Untick the checkbox beside the Keyman keyboard.</p></li><li><p>Click <span class="guibutton">OK</span>.</p></li></ol></div><p>When a keyboard layout is disabled, its name appears in grey and its checkbox is unticked.</p><h3><a name="id569195"></a>Enabling a Keyman keyboard</h3><p>To enable a Keyman keyboard:</p><div class="orderedlist"><ol type="1"><li><p>Open <span class="application">Keyman Desktop</span>.</p></li><li><p>Click on the <span class="guiicon">Keyman Desktop</span> icon <span class="inlinemediaobject"><img src="desktop_images/icon-keyman.png"></span>, on the Windows Taskbar near the clock.</p><p>
        <span class="inlinemediaobject"><img src="desktop_images/menu.png"></span>
      </p></li><li><p>Select Configuration.</p><p>
        <span class="inlinemediaobject"><img src="desktop_images/tab-layout.png"></span>
      </p></li><li><p>Select the Keyboard Layouts tab.</p></li><li><p>Tick the checkbox beside the Keyman keyboard.</p></li><li><p>Click <span class="guibutton">OK</span>.</p></li></ol></div><h3><a name="id569301"></a>Related Topics</h3><div class="itemizedlist"><ul type="disc"><li><p>
        <a class="xref" href="basic_uninstall_keyboard.php" title="Keyboard Task - Uninstall a Keyboard">Keyboard Task - Uninstall a Keyboard</a>
      </p></li><li><p>
        <a class="xref" href="basic_enable_keyboard.php" title="Keyboard Task - Turn on a Keyboard">Keyboard Task - Turn on a Keyboard</a>
      </p></li><li><p>
        <a class="xref" href="basic_keyboards_tab.php" title="Keyman Configuration - Keyboard Layouts Tab">Keyman Configuration - Keyboard Layouts Tab</a>
      </p></li></ul></div></div><div class="navfooter"><hr><table width="100%" summary="Navigation footer"><tr><td width="40%" align="left"><a accesskey="p" href="basic_enable_keyboard.php">Prev</a> </td><td width="20%" align="center"><a accesskey="u" href="basic.php">Up</a></td><td width="40%" align="right"> <a accesskey="n" href="basic_uninstall_keyboard.php">Next</a></td></tr><tr><td width="40%" align="left" valign="top">Keyboard Task - Turn on a Keyboard </td><td width="20%" align="center"><a accesskey="h" href="index.php">Home</a></td><td width="40%" align="right" valign="top"> Keyboard Task - Uninstall a Keyboard</td></tr></table></div>
